results.name: a(n) = the number of positive divisors of n which are coprime to d(n), where d(n) = the number of positive divisors of n.
link: Harvey P. Dale, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
example: The 6 positive divisors of 20 are 1,2,4,5,10,20. Of these, only 1 and 5 are coprime to d(20) = 6. So a(20) = 2.
maple: with(numtheory): a:=proc(n) local div,ct,i: div:=divisors(n): ct:=0: for i from 1 to tau(n) do if igcd(div[i],tau(n))=1 then ct:=ct+1 else ct:=ct: fi od: ct; end: seq(a(n),n=1..140); # _Emeric Deutsch_, Apr 14 2007
